author: John Whitesides
title: Wisconsin pushes ahead with presidential primary despite coronavirus fears
description: After a flurry of 11th-hour legal action failed to stop the balloting, Wisconsin voters will head to the polls for a presidential primary and state and local elections on Tuesday despite mounting fears about health risks from the coronavirus.
content:
